            <![CDATA[
                    <p><img src="https://Jefff-yu.github.io/Jefffyu/media/posts/6/Jie-Tu-2023-10-02-12.44.36.png" class="type:primaryImage" alt="&quot;Tossed Amidst the Waves”" /></p>
                
    <h2 id="sui-lang-hua-hun-chen">
      隨浪花昏沉
    </h2>

  <p>
    隨浪花昏沉<br><br>單頻道音像 / 1280*720 / 2:40 / 2023年<br>Tochdesigner、Ableton Live
  </p>

  <p>
    Single-channel audiovisual / 1280*720 / 2:40 / 2023<br>Tochdesigner, Ableton Live
  </p>

  <p>
    「隨浪花昏沉 」發想自從新竹回到家鄉台東後的經歷，原以為去看海可以讓人放鬆身心， 結果因為還有事情沒有做完，去到的海岸也並非想像中的沙灘而是礫灘。海浪聲沒有撫慰我。 我反而注視著濺起的浪花，混雜著回到家的快樂，和一些難以言說的惆悵與慵懶的氣息。<br><br>/<br><br>"Tossed Amidst the Waves"<br><br>The inspiration for "Tossed Amidst the Waves" stems from my experiences returning to my hometown, Taitung, after being in Hsinchu. Initially, I thought a visit to the sea would bring relaxation to my mind and body. However, the reality differed as there were unfinished tasks, and the coastal area I arrived at was not the sandy beach I had imagined, but rather a pebble shore. The sound of the waves did not soothe me. Instead, I found myself fixated on the splashing seafoam, a mix of the joy of returning home and an indescribable sense of melancholy and languor.
  </p>

